   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Food Security in Kigutu, Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Village Health Works (VHW), located in Kigutu, Burundi, offers community, clinical, and school-based programs with an impact on more than 200,000 community members in the last year. To relieve Burundi of the title, &quot;Hungriest Country in the World,&quot; according to the 2014 Global Hunger Index, VHW addresses sustainable agriculture and livestock care through supporting on-site and household gardens. Increased harvests provide local families, patients, and school children with nutritious meals.</narrative>
  </description>
